# Build-context hygiene + defense-in-depth: nothing secret or heavy enters the
# build context (the Dockerfile does NOT COPY repo source — it is bind-mounted at
# runtime — but this keeps the context small and blocks accidental future COPY of
# secrets). Mirrors .gitignore + the host-config / node_modules surfaces.

# Secrets — never in the build context (public-repo safe)
.env
**/.env
*.pem
*.key
secrets/

# Host CLI-config + signing-key dirs — defense-in-depth.
# The structural defense is already in place: the Dockerfile contains ZERO
# COPY/ADD directives (source enters at runtime via bind-mount, not build),
# so these dirs CANNOT enter a layer today. The exclusions below guarantee
# the safety property holds if a future Dockerfile ever adds a `COPY .` line.
**/.claude
**/.codex
**/.gemini
**/.gnupg

# VCS + per-session state
.git
**/.session-notes
.claude/learning/

# Installed/generated artifacts (installed at runtime, not baked)
**/node_modules
.codex-mcp-guard/node_modules
**/__pycache__/
**/.venv/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/

# Workspace process artifacts (not part of the image)
workspaces/

# Project-owned populated overlays (defense-in-depth — these never belong in
# the image build context; populated forms may carry host-specific values).
compose.override.yml
*.local
Gemfile.user.lock

# OS cruft
**/.DS_Store
